        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! Circuit built. Here's your wiring table and sketch summary:\n\n**Wiring Table:**\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Pin |\n|---|---|---|\n| D2 | 7-seg Display | a (via R_a 220Ω) |\n| D3 | 7-seg Display | b (via R_b 220Ω) |\n| D4 | 7-seg Display | c (via R_c 220Ω) |\n| D5 | 7-seg Display | d (via R_d 220Ω) |\n| D6 | 7-seg Display | e (via R_e 220Ω) |\n| D7 | 7-seg Display | f (via R_f 220Ω) |\n| D8 | 7-seg Display | g (via R_g 220Ω) |\n| D9 | Button | pin a |\n| GND | 7-seg Display | gnd |\n| GND | Button | pin b |\n\n**Sketch Summary:**\nThe sketch maintains a global `counter` variable (0–9). Each button press (detected via INPUT_PULLUP active-LOW) increments the counter and wraps around at 10. A `displayDigit()` function maps each digit to the correct 7-segment pattern (which segments light up) and writes them to pins D2–D8. The display updates immediately on each button press with 50ms debounce."
